article.headline: N. Arizona 91, E. Washington 80
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- Stephen Sir came off the bench to score 25 points to lead Northern Arizona to a 91-80 victory over Eastern Washington on Thursday night. Sir, last week's Big Sky Conference player of the week, was 7-for-10 from 3-point range and has now made 26 of his last 34 shots (76 percent) from there. Fellow reserve Tyrone Bazy added 19 points and Josh Wilson had a career-high 14 assists for the Lumberjacks (10-8, 5-2 Big Sky). They used a 12-2 second-half burst to pull away from the Eagles (9-10, 3-4). Rodney Stuckey scored 24 points and had eight rebounds and dive assists to lead Eastern Washington. With Northern Arizona clinging to a 57-56 lead with 11 minutes left, Sir made a 3 to begin the Lumberjacks' decisive run. Ryan McCurdy, who finished with 18 points, scored back-to-back baskets inside to give Northern Arizona a 69-58 advantage with 7:55 left. EWU never got closer than seven the rest of the way. Paul Butorac added 16 points and Kellen Williams 10 for the Eagles, who shot 57 percent from the floor but struggled from the line (8-for-22) and 3-point range (2-for-14). Northern Arizona, which finished 12 of 20 from 3-point range, got 11 rebounds from Ruben Boykin Jr. The Lumberjacks' bench outscored EWU's 48-23.
